 me it usually isn't the Chanters and Clerics.. it's the raid leader. You know, that guy that spends a couple hours shepherding us into groups and through the buffing lines, forming up the groups and probably pulling his fewl hair out the whole time ;p Sure, some of that cost is recouped from the coin dropped by Giants during clearing, but I'm willing to bet not all, maybe not even half. Lets do the raid leader a favor and make his job a little bit easier by bringing a peridot or two to the next raid. I know I will be.<br><br>Peace<br>Al <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujuliksupermonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Julik Supermonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/01 11:42:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverndragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1140.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gigahosts.com/~c1003/aimicons/icons/comicsdc/superman2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cost of a Dragon Raid</span><hr size=1> Lol yeah cost me about that my first Raid.. and i didn't get to loot any giants <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    When i did it i hadnt heard of a vox raid in a long time and really wanted a bag so i spent a day or so gaining some money and led one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Ended up winnign the bag my first raid so i didn't have to spend much more... But If you ever wonder why people call items on raids that is why.. it would suck to spend 1200pp and be stressed out for a good 3 or 4 <br>hours and walk away with nothing but a nice jo